ðŸ”¹ 2. File Viewing and Editing
Command	Description
cat	Concatenate and display file content
more / less	View file content page by page
head	Show first 10 lines of a file
tail	Show last 10 lines of a file
nano, vim, vi	Command-line text editors
cut	Remove sections from each line of files
wc	Count lines, words, characters
sort, uniq	Sort lines or find unique lines

ðŸ”¹ 3. System Information
Command	Description
uname -a	All system information
top / htop	Real-time system resource usage
uptime	System uptime
hostname	Show system hostname
whoami	Current logged-in user
id	Show user ID and group
df -h	Disk space usage
du -sh	Disk usage of a folder
free -h	Memory usage
lscpu, lsblk, lsusb, lspci	Show CPU, block devices, USB, PCI info

ðŸ”¹ 4. Package Management (Depends on distro)
For Debian/Ubuntu:
Command	Description
apt update	Refresh package list
apt upgrade	Upgrade all packages
apt install <package>	Install package
apt remove <package>	Remove package
dpkg -i	Install .deb package

For Red Hat/CentOS:
Command	Description
yum install <package>	Install using YUM
dnf install <package>	Newer YUM replacement

ðŸ”¹ 5. User Management
Command	Description
adduser <username>	Add user
passwd <username>	Set/change password
deluser <username>	Delete user
usermod -aG <group> <user>	Add user to group
groups	Show userâ€™s groups

ðŸ”¹ 6. Permissions & Ownership
Command	Description
chmod	Change file permissions
chown	Change file owner
chgrp	Change file group
umask	Show default permission mask

ðŸ”¹ 7. Process Management
Command	Description
ps	View current processes
kill <pid>	Kill process by PID
killall <name>	Kill process by name
bg / fg	Background/foreground process control
jobs	List background jobs
nice, renice	Set priority of processes

ðŸ”¹ 8. Networking
Command	Description
ping <host>	Ping a server
ifconfig / ip a	Show IP addresses
netstat -tulnp	Show open ports
ss -tuln	Socket statistics
traceroute <host>	Trace route to host
wget <url>	Download from the web
curl <url>	Transfer data from or to a server

ðŸ”¹ 9. Archiving & Compression
Command	Description
tar -cvf	Create tar file
tar -xvf	Extract tar file
gzip, gunzip	Compress/uncompress using gzip
zip, unzip	Compress/uncompress zip files

ðŸ”¹ 10. Shell and Scripting
Command	Description
echo	Print a message
read	Read input
alias	Create command shortcut
history	Show command history
bash, sh	Start a shell
source file.sh	Run script in current shell

ðŸ”¹ 11. Disk and Partition Management
Command	Description
fdisk	Partition table manipulator
mount, umount	Mount/unmount file systems
mkfs	Format disk
fsck	Check and repair file systems

ðŸ”¹ 12. Logs and System Monitoring
Command	Description
dmesg	Boot and kernel messages
journalctl	View systemd logs
tail -f /var/log/syslog	Live system logs
